Fine particulate matter emission in counties of USA

Oksana Volnianska
25.03.2016

About application

  • This app is showing the PM25 emission by source type across the United States counties that are located on US choropleth.

    • Fine particulate matter (PM2.5) is an ambient air pollutant for which there is strong evidence that it is harmful to human health. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) releases its database on emissions of PM2.5 for the USA. For each year and for each type of PM source, the data records show how many tons of PM2.5 were emitted. The original data set was obtained from https://d396qusza40orc.cloudfront.net/exdata%2Fdata%2FNEI_data.zip and contains the data for the folowing years: 1999, 2002, 2005,and 2008. For app use reduced data set for 2002-2008 and only two type source.The data set includes fips and names of counties in USA obtained from RDDAP data server http://coastwatch.pfeg.noaa.gov/erddap/convert/fipscounty.html .

  • shiny package facilitates making web app for R
  • sqldf, tcltk packages use SQL for R data.frame
  • ggplot2 package for making plot in app R
  • choroplethr, choroplethrMaps packages for making geographic map of the US

    • Example data set for selected county

    getCountyEmissions() function build query uncluding the data from two based data sets (see Page 2 of a presentation).

    getCountyEmissions <- function(name) {
  code <- subset(c_unique, county==name)$fips
  sql_query <-paste("SELECT year as Year, type as Type, county,                     sum(Emissions) as Emission, fips FROM NEI JOIN fcc USING (fips) WHERE fips =",as.character(code)," GROUP BY fips, year, type")
  out<-sqldf(sql_query)
  return(out)
}

    It is example data for county = “FL, Palm Beach”:
